[5] Cases in various countries: Venezuela, Brazil, Martinique and
Guadeloupe, Taiwan, India

- Venezuela, 29 Oct 2010: according to the most recent
epidemiological bulletin of the Ministry of Health published this
Thursday (28 Oct 2010) up to 9 Oct 2010, this year 99 178 dengue
cases were registered, 8916 of which were DHF cases. This is an
increase of more than 160 percent compared to the same period last
year (2009), when 39 004 dengue cases were registered. The dengue
epidemic is declining in 15 states but continues in 8
(<http://www.eluniversal.com/2010/10/28/pol_ava_venezuela-registra-m_28A4664173.shtml>
in Spanish).

- Brazil (Sao Paulo), 26 Oct 2010: dengue continues claiming victims
in all of Sao Paulo state. This report indicates the numbers of cases
and deaths in various cities and regions in the state
(<http://g1.globo.com/sao-paulo/noticia/2010/10/baixada-santista-sofre-com-epidemia-de-dengue.html>
in Portuguese).

- Brazil (Minas Gerais), 28 Oct 2010: in Belo Horizone 146 dengue
cases have been registered in recent weeks with 91 cases just last
week [week of 18 Oct 2010]. In total this year (2010), 67 414 cases
have been registered in this state capital city
(<http://www.band.com.br/jornalismo/saude/conteudo.asp?ID=100000362322>
in Portuguese).

- Brazil (Mato Grosso), 28 Oct 2010: a total of 62 reported dengue
deaths were reported in Mato Grosso of which 52 were confirmed and 10
are under investigation. From 1 Jan - 28 Oct 2010, 42 350 dengue
cases have been reported in the state
(<http://www.expressomt.com.br/noticiaBusca.asp?cod=99776&codDep=3>
in Portuguese).

- Martinique and Guadeloupe, 29 Oct 2010: with 220 clinically
suggestive cases during the week of 18-24 Oct 2010, against 329
during the previous week, the dengue epidemic continues to decline in
Martinique. Some 41 700 clinically suggestive cases of dengue were
reported in Martinique since the outbreak began last February (2010),
including 634 hospitalized patients and 16 deaths directly or
indirectly associated with the disease. In Guadeloupe, with 238
clinically suggestive cases during the week of 18-24 Oct [2010],
against 162 during the previous week, the decline in the epidemic has
stopped. Health officials from Guadeloupe have identified nearly 43
800 clinically suggestive cases of dengue fever since the beginning
of the epidemic in December 2009, including 5 deaths directly or
indirectly related to dengue
(<http://sante-medecine.commentcamarche.net/news/111679-dengue-vers-la-fin-de-l-epidemie-en-martinique>
in French).

- Taiwan, 27 Oct 2010: dengue cases hit a record high this week, with
156 cases nationwide, 139 of them in the southern cities of Kaohsiung
and Tainan. There has been a 3rd locally acquired dengue case in
Taipei in 2010.
(<http://www.chinapost.com.tw/taiwan/national/national-news/2010/10/27/277620/North-joins.htm>).

- India (Lucknow), 28 Oct 2010: according to health department
officials in Lucknow, 4 more persons, including a 3-year-old girl,
died of suspected dengue taking the death toll to 61 in the state
(<http://ibnlive.in.com/generalnewsfeed/news/four-more-die-of-suspected-dengue-toll-reaches-61/453354.html>).

India (Delhi), 28 Oct 2010: the number of dengue cases in the capital
continued to rise, with 75 more cases reported Thu 28 Oct 2010,
taking the total this season to 5363
(<http://sify.com/news/75-more-infected-with-dengue-in-delhi-news-health-kk2sOuidcfa.html>).

